result.execSummary:
The defendant Stefany D. Szemraj was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess Amphetamine/LSD/Psilocin, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(d).
  • Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes:
Jackson County case 14CF63, Possesion of Drug Paraphernalia to manufacture etc, 961.573(3) was dismissed and read-in to this case.  The defendant shall pay Department of Correction fees as directed by the agent.  Defendant was ordered to report immediately to the probation and parole office.
Concurrent with: Probation on counts 1&2 to run concurrent to each other as are the conditions thereof unless otherwise specified.

miscConds.notes: Costs paid from bond previously posted.
Defendant shall attend counseling, treatments, programming, evaluations as deemed appropriate by the agent releasing all records to the agent upon request

Defendant shall not possess or consume any alcohol, and not go into places that sell alcohol except incidentally such as a grocery store, convenience store or gas station or other such place where alcohol is not sold for consumption on the premises.  
The defendant shall submit to random urine/PBT testing as required by the agent or any law enforcement officer .
Cell phone and Samsung tablet seized in this case maybe returned to the defendant after 2-23-2015 if no appeal has been filed.
The defendant is to submit to an Alcohol and Other Drug Assessment (AODA) and follow the recommendations, releasing the findings to the agent.

supervisions.notes:
Conditions of probation are the same for counts 1&2, See Count 1 for conditions.
Concurrent with: Probation on counts 1&2 to run concurrent to each other as are the conditions thereof unless otherwise specified.
